article.headline: UTEP 89, Alabama State 57
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Omar Thomas scored 33 points to lead Texas-El Paso to an 89-57 victory over Alabama State on Monday in the first round of the Sun Bowl Tournament. Thomas had six rebounds and was 7-of-10 from the free-throw line. He was 13-of-17 from the field. Filiberto Rivera scored 14 points and had 12 assists for Texas-El Paso (9-2), and John Tofi added 10 points. George Savage had a team-high 18 points for the Hornets (2-6), who only shot 39 percent from the field. The Miners took a 46-24 lead into halftime. The game was decided in the first 12 minutes of play. Texas El-Paso, which scored 33 points off 28 Alabama State turnovers, will take on Princeton on Tuesday. The Tigers defeated Tulane 59-51 in the other first-round game. Alabama State will play Tulane for third place.
